description: Jimmy Heath, at the Barnes & Noble, NYC discussion and signing celebrating the release of his autobiography, I Walked with Giants. Jimmy riffs on his boyhood and coming of age as a young musician in Philadelphia; the music giants whom he loved, admired and played with; his spectacular life connections—good and bad; his beloved one-of-a-kind brother Percy; and the joy of sharing music and the bandstand with his brilliant siblings. Introduced by co-author Joseph McLaren, Jimmy spoke to a packed house. Celebrating with him and McLaren were the beautiful Mona Heath, fans, musicians, journalists, and jazz cognoscenti including Jean Bach, Phoebe Jacobs, Rene McLean, Jon and Laurelyn Faddis, David Wong, Phil and Toni Terman, Carol Friedman, Jeb Patton, Wendy Oxenhorn, Jonathan Sanoff, Larry Ridley, nephew Percy Heath 3rd, Kit McLure, Wyatt Leach and Karen Chester, among others.  I Walked with Giants, by Jimmy Heath and Joseph McLaren, with a foreword by Bill Cosby and introduction by Wynton Marsalis. Temple University Press.
